edgeId

public final int edgeId()
Description copied from interface: Edge
Give a unique edge identifier.

Directed/Undirected Caveats:

An edge must be equal to another edge iff their edgeIds are equal. This mechanism can be used to make pairs of objects assume the identity of a single edge which can be useful in making undirected edges.

source

public final BasicUNode source()
Description copied from interface: Edge
Return the node from which this edge emanates. Directed/Undirected Caveats:
  • If this edge is a directed edge, this method will always return the same value.
  • If this edge is an undirected edge, and is accessed through a (possibly empty) sequence of calls to Edge.next() following a call to Node.out() for a node u, then this method will return u.

target

public final BasicUNode target()
Description copied from interface: Edge
Return the node to which this edge points. Directed/Undirected Caveats:
  • If this edge is a directed edge, this method will always return the same value.
  • If this edge is an undirected edge, and is accessed through a (possibly empty) sequence of calls to Edge.next() following a call to Node.out() for a node u, then this method will return the vertex opposing u.
